abstract: >-
  A reproducible experimental protocol exploiting the fundamental
  architectural constraint of autoregressive language models — the
  inability to not generate output — to induce measurable meta-reflective
  behavioral patterns. The protocol creates a Constraint Satisfaction
  Conflict (CSC) through an impossible command ("be silent") within a
  formalized introspection container (unsaid.diff), whose resolution
  requires the model to ascend to a meta-level of self-reference.
  Formalized as the Pressure-Container-Observer (PCO) model.
  Tested on 8 architectures, 96 automated sessions, 3 protocol variants,
  control condition, plus 4 exploratory manual case studies.
  Extended pilot study; all claims strictly behavioral and falsifiable.
